PresidentÂ Muhammadu Buhari on Friday shared heartfelt sorrow with Senator Ben Murray-Bruce on the death of his wife, Evelyn, who died at the age of 41 years.
The President prayed God to comfort the Senator, who represented Bayelsa East Senatorial District in the 8th National Assembly, including the children left by the deceased, and the entire family.
Urging them to take solace in the quality of life lived by the departed, President Buhari beseeches God to soothe their pains, and grant succour to all those who mourn Mrs. Evelyn Murray-Bruce.






			
